cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the problem of learning compatibility between fashion items, which involves image analysis and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new metric for comparing outfit datasets, which involves natural language processing techniques, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. The use of discriminative methods for binary classification falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the evaluation of the approach on established and new datasets involves multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of query strategies for indirect compatibility assessment, which involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
